    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Belgium/277: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-07T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 7, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 7—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Department’s 20, June 25, 5 p.m., and my 44, June 26, 7 p.m.<note n="25"
                        xml:id="d334fn25">Neither printed.</note> Costermans has just informed me
                    that the Belgian Ministry of Finance has approved new regulations providing that
                    shipment of alcohol from Belgium shall henceforth be restricted to vessels of
                    regular route and itinerary and minimum tonnage of 3000 tons net and to barrels
                    containing 100 liters which he declares will weigh about 200 kilograms and will
                    be too heavy to transship at sea without the aid of a crane. Costermans stated
                    that a decree will be signed by the Minister of Finance in a few days and that
                    the new regulations will then be put into effect as an administrative
                    measure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
